HEADWORD: Jane
<hw>Jane</hw> <pr>(j⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>Janua</ets> Genoa; L. <ets>Genua</ets>, also OE.
<ets>Jean</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A coin of Genoa; any small
coin.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of twilled cotton cloth. See
<er>Jean</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

